info.headline: Fire Weather Watch issued May 28 at 9:29PM CDT until May 29 at 9:00PM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...FIRE WEATHER WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM MONDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH MONDAY EVENING FOR WIND AND LOW RELATIVE HUMIDITY FOR FAR NORTH CENTRAL AND NORTHEASTERN MINNESOTA... ...RED FLAG WARNING HAS EXPIRED FOR WIND AND LOW RELATIVE HUMIDITY FOR ALL OF NORTH CENTRAL MINNESOTA AND PARTS OF NORTHEAST MINNESOTA... * AFFECTED AREA...In Minnesota, Koochiching, North St. Louis, Northern Cook and Lake, North Itasca, Central St. Louis and South Itasca. * WINDS...South 10 to 15 mph with gusts up to 25 mph. * RELATIVE HUMIDITY...As low as 14 percent. * TEMPERATURES...In the low 80s. * IMPACTS...Any fires may grow and spread quickly.
info.instruction: A Fire Weather Watch means that critical fire weather conditions are forecast to occur. Listen for later forecasts and possible Red Flag Warnings.
